import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['location', 'precipitation']]
    seattle_precipitation = data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']['precipitation']
    new_york_precipitation = data[data['location'] == 'New York']['precipitation']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot([seattle_precipitation, new_york_precipitation], labels=['Seattle', 'New York'])
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of precipitation in Seattle and New York?')
    ax.set_ylabel('Precipitation')
    ax.set_xlabel('Location')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by=['date'])
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['temp_max'], label='Maximum Temperature')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['temp_min'], label='Minimum Temperature')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature (°C)')
    plt.title('How does the temperature vary over time in Seattle?')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind speed and temperature in New York?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data['count'] = 1
    data = data.groupby(['location', 'weather']).count().reset_index()
    seattle_data = data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']
    ny_data = data[data['location'] == 'New York']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(seattle_data['weather'], seattle_data['count'], label='Seattle')
    ax.bar(ny_data['weather'], ny_data['count'], label='New York')
    ax.set_xlabel('Weather Condition')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common weather condition in Seattle and New York?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']
    data = data[['precipitation', 'temp_max']]
    plt.scatter(data['precipitation'], data['temp_max'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Precipitation')
    plt.ylabel('Maximum Temperature')
    plt.title('How does precipitation affect temperature in Seattle?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
